00:23:04,319 --> 00:23:07,490
You should make sure
Father doesn't drink or smoke.

257
00:23:08,759 --> 00:23:10,759
Since Mother has bad knees,

258
00:23:11,359 --> 00:23:13,930
you should run her errands
whenever she asks.

259
00:23:15,329 --> 00:23:16,769
As for my guitar,

260
00:23:17,269 --> 00:23:20,539
please burn it and bury it with me.

261
00:23:23,069 --> 00:23:26,210
Yong Sik!

262
00:23:26,210 --> 00:23:27,539
Let's get out of here.

263
00:23:34,619 --> 00:23:35,920
Hwang Pil Sun.

264
00:23:36,819 --> 00:23:38,990
You're worse than your mother.

265
00:23:39,759 --> 00:23:42,190
You will die a horrible death.

266
00:23:43,089 --> 00:23:47,099
In the most unsightly way possible.

267
00:24:54,970 --> 00:24:56,069
Mom!

268
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,839
Mom. Mom!

269
00:25:00,839 --> 00:25:02,009
(For orchards and weeds)

270
00:25:02,869 --> 00:25:04,640
What's the matter?

271
00:25:05,509 --> 00:25:06,640
Why did you...

272
00:25:08,980 --> 00:25:10,549
come so late?

273
00:25:11,079 --> 00:25:13,319
Mom, what's the matter?

274
00:25:14,079 --> 00:25:15,549
My dear Jae Gyu.

275
00:25:18,819 --> 00:25:20,660
You must become a big person.

276
00:25:21,319 --> 00:25:22,589
Mom.

277
00:25:30,329 --> 00:25:31,470
There's rice...

278
00:25:33,069 --> 00:25:34,769
in the pot.

279
00:25:37,839 --> 00:25:39,079
Eat it...

280
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:41,779
before it gets cold.

281
00:25:46,279 --> 00:25:48,650
Mom! Mom!

282
00:25:49,750 --> 00:25:52,519
The day Jin Jae Gyu saw his ability,

283
00:25:52,890 --> 00:25:54,089
Mom!

284
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:55,690
his mother died.

285
00:25:56,029 --> 00:25:57,490
Mom!

286
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:00,130
She drank pesticide?

287
00:26:00,130 --> 00:26:02,329
But why is his ability so important?

288
00:26:02,329 --> 00:26:03,970
What does it have to do
with you coming here?

289
00:26:06,769 --> 00:26:07,900
It was his last words.

290
00:26:08,869 --> 00:26:10,569
You'll meet him again.

291
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:12,640
He predicted we'd meet again.

292
00:26:13,509 --> 00:26:17,079
After Dong Baek disappears,
you'll find him at the altar.

293
00:26:17,609 --> 00:26:19,519
The altar of the murderer.

294
00:26:20,279 --> 00:26:21,690
Did you come looking for me here...

295
00:26:22,849 --> 00:26:24,150
just because of what he said?

296
00:26:26,390 --> 00:26:28,630
How many dying words did he say?

297
00:26:29,329 --> 00:26:30,359
He told me four things.

298
00:26:31,289 --> 00:26:33,660
He said the Eraser is hiding
in your past,

299
00:26:34,230 --> 00:26:36,470
and that I would
meet you again here.

300
00:26:36,869 --> 00:26:37,970
Lastly,

301
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:41,039
he told me to look for the meadow.

302
00:26:42,210 --> 00:26:44,710
- There's still one more.
- This one was the strangest.

303
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:47,940
The night Park Gi Dan died,

304
00:26:49,509 --> 00:26:51,680
he said someone paid a visit
to the prayer house.

305
00:26:53,779 --> 00:26:54,950
None other than...

306
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:00,059
you.

307
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:02,589
I saw a revelation.

308
00:27:05,299 --> 00:27:07,660
I saw him standing there.

309
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,269
Of course, I ignored it.

310
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:11,769
I thought he was losing his mind
as he faded away.

311
00:27:13,170 --> 00:27:16,539
But, his last words became reality
and I changed my mind.

312
00:27:17,309 --> 00:27:19,240
If Jin Jae Gyu can really
predict the future,

313
00:27:20,579 --> 00:27:24,079
that makes it more likely for you
to have gone to the prayer house.

314
00:27:28,549 --> 00:27:29,849
Did you kill Park Gi Dan?

315
00:27:32,589 --> 00:27:33,720
I wanted to kill him.

316
00:27:34,890 --> 00:27:37,160
I wanted to ask him how it feels
to get punished the same way...

317
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:40,529
before he took his last breath.

318
00:27:41,970 --> 00:27:43,069
Yes.

319
00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:46,069
It's true. I was there.

320
00:27:47,769 --> 00:27:49,109
But I went to read his memories.

321
00:27:49,809 --> 00:27:51,369
Since I was due
to get arrested anyway,

322
00:27:52,140 --> 00:27:54,380
I wanted to reveal his crimes
to the world.

323
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:58,079
And?

324
00:28:00,319 --> 00:28:01,519
I turned around and left...

325
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:03,390
the prayer house.

326
00:28:04,289 --> 00:28:05,490
But you went all the way there.

327
00:28:07,460 --> 00:28:08,529
I was reminded...

328
00:28:10,859 --> 00:28:12,930
of an incident from a long time ago.

329
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:19,339
The window I would always look at
after Meadow disappeared.

330
00:28:21,140 --> 00:28:22,309
That's when I realized...

331
00:28:23,710 --> 00:28:25,109
she would never want me...

332
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:28,750
to act this way.

333
00:28:32,150 --> 00:28:33,519
Meadow always wanted...

334
00:28:34,619 --> 00:28:36,619
everyone to know my ability...

335
00:28:36,619 --> 00:28:39,490
so that the world would
become kinder.

336
00:28:42,559 --> 00:28:43,890
That woman named Ko Hyun A...

337
00:28:44,329 --> 00:28:46,660
was on her way back with her
secret lover after a date.

338
00:28:56,710 --> 00:28:57,740
- What is it?
- What was that?

339
00:29:00,579 --> 00:29:03,210
- What now?
- Over here.

340
00:29:05,519 --> 00:29:06,819
- Hurry up.
- Hold on.

341
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:08,490
Darn it.

342
00:29:09,490 --> 00:29:11,250
Please help me...

343
00:29:15,460 --> 00:29:17,160
- She must be alive.
- Darn it.

344
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,390
Please help me...

345
00:29:21,359 --> 00:29:23,369
Gosh. What are you doing?

346
00:29:23,829 --> 00:29:25,440
- What are you doing?
- Out of my way!

347
00:29:26,269 --> 00:29:28,339
No. No!

348
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,670
I'm Ko Hyun A.

349
00:29:30,940 --> 00:29:32,609
It was the day after...

350
00:29:33,380 --> 00:29:34,779
when I met her.

351
00:29:36,849 --> 00:29:37,950
Had I...

352
00:29:39,279 --> 00:29:41,079
shook her hand then...

353
00:29:43,589 --> 00:29:45,089
Had I shook her hand...

354
00:29:49,490 --> 00:29:51,930
And you came out
so you could convict the murderers.

355
00:29:55,630 --> 00:29:56,769
How did you know that?

356
00:29:58,230 --> 00:30:01,140
My trial record is a state secret.

357
00:30:02,839 --> 00:30:04,039
You owe me.

358
00:30:08,009 --> 00:30:09,109
National Intelligence Service?

359
00:30:09,509 --> 00:30:10,809
Good guess.

360
00:30:11,710 --> 00:30:13,619
You knew everything,
so you were just watching me.

361
00:30:14,519 --> 00:30:17,849
What now?
Are you going to arrest me?

362
00:30:18,250 --> 00:30:21,690
No, you're not the type
to ever commit murder.

363
00:30:22,890 --> 00:30:24,960
What I've been suspicious about...

364
00:30:26,230 --> 00:30:27,460
is a split personality.

365
00:30:29,930 --> 00:30:32,700
The evil personality
that killed 7...

366
00:30:33,339 --> 00:30:34,470
in Shimbae City 20 years ago.

367
00:30:36,470 --> 00:30:38,470
What if your other personality
worked with an accomplice...

368
00:30:38,470 --> 00:30:39,740
and acted as the Eraser?

369
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:42,750
I'm not in the mood to joke.

370
00:30:43,349 --> 00:30:46,549
I tried profiling,
and there was zero possibility.

371
00:30:47,150 --> 00:30:50,519
Unless you're using a huge trick
I can't wrap my head around.

372
00:30:50,990 --> 00:30:52,059
So?

373
00:30:56,029 --> 00:30:57,460
I trust you, Det. Dong.

374
00:30:57,890 --> 00:30:58,900
No.

375
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:01,029
I trust my judgment.

376
00:31:01,599 --> 00:31:04,769
Is the interrogation over?

377
00:31:07,299 --> 00:31:08,299
For now.

378
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:12,839
I'm so thankful.

379
00:31:14,079 --> 00:31:17,380
That's why we'll work together
until we catch the Eraser.

380
00:31:27,460 --> 00:31:29,390
In the end, what's left
is the case from Shimbae City.

381
00:31:29,759 --> 00:31:32,829
I'm certain another person
was in that warehouse.

382
00:31:34,799 --> 00:31:36,670
They were over 170cm tall.

383
00:31:37,170 --> 00:31:39,339
When the culprit killed seven people
in Shimbae City,

384
00:31:39,369 --> 00:31:41,470
the young Det. Dong was there.

385
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:42,970
Mom.

386
00:31:42,970 --> 00:31:45,309
He even killed
your mother that night.

387
00:31:46,740 --> 00:31:49,410
You were wandering after losing
your memory when you were found.

388
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,779
Why do you think the Eraser
was called the Young Devil?

389
00:31:55,349 --> 00:31:56,690
He must have been young.

390
00:31:57,119 --> 00:31:59,859
At the time, Moon Yong Gwang
was only 17 years old.

391
00:32:01,819 --> 00:32:03,230
Do you think Moon Yong Gwang
is the Eraser?

392
00:32:03,230 --> 00:32:05,960
The Eraser must have an ill
relationship with your family,

393
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,599
and he also killed seven people.

394
00:32:08,230 --> 00:32:09,970
But two months before
the incident happened,

395
00:32:10,269 --> 00:32:12,400
Moon Yong Gwang's big brother
was killed mysteriously.

396
00:32:13,339 --> 00:32:15,609
Did he avenge his brother because
those seven were responsible?

397
00:32:16,240 --> 00:32:17,309
By becoming the Eraser?

398
00:32:17,910 --> 00:32:20,680
Even if he's not the Eraser,
the two of them are accomplices.

399
00:32:21,140 --> 00:32:22,210
How so?

400
00:32:22,710 --> 00:32:25,279
If I was the Eraser,
I would make sure to keep...

401
00:32:25,279 --> 00:32:26,720
a good card like Moon Yong Gwang
with me.

402
00:32:27,019 --> 00:32:28,420
It's similar to the way
he used Jin Jae Gyu.

403
00:32:29,990 --> 00:32:32,460
Then why did Moon Yong Gwang leak
Deputy Chief Lee's information?

404
00:32:34,559 --> 00:32:35,759
To confuse us?

405
00:32:36,890 --> 00:32:39,130
I'm sure Eraser
has a bigger picture.

406
00:32:39,730 --> 00:32:42,269
We don't know
his ultimate objective yet.

407
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:43,670
"His ultimate objective"?

408
00:32:44,130 --> 00:32:45,599
The one
who instigated Lee Shin Woong.

409
00:32:48,039 --> 00:32:50,569
So there's an evildoer
who instigated the scattered cases?

410
00:32:50,569 --> 00:32:52,609
And that's the ultimate objective
of the Eraser?

411
00:32:54,210 --> 00:32:56,549
Then we have the answer.
We either strike Lee Shin Woong...

412
00:32:56,549 --> 00:32:59,250
or crack Moon Yong Gwang
who's the Eraser's accomplice.

413
00:32:59,319 --> 00:33:00,349
What should we do first?

414
00:33:00,380 --> 00:33:02,990
You should stay out of it.
It's on me now.

415
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:05,519
- What?
- You might end up dead.

416
00:33:08,490 --> 00:33:09,960
Did Professor Ahn talk again?

417
00:33:10,460 --> 00:33:12,400
My condition is a national secret.

418
00:33:12,829 --> 00:33:15,029
She tends to overact.

419
00:33:19,339 --> 00:33:22,769
Rest here. It's not wiretapped,
so keep it on.

420
00:33:24,269 --> 00:33:25,710
Are you going to chase clues
without me?

421
00:33:27,009 --> 00:33:28,480
You'll only get in the way
in your current condition.

422
00:33:32,819 --> 00:33:34,250
This is my fight.

423
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:36,519
I can't stop even if it kills me.

424
00:33:40,589 --> 00:33:42,160
I have a lead...

425
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:44,660
on the one
who's helping Moon Yong Gwang.

426
00:33:46,529 --> 00:33:47,630
Who is it?

427
00:33:49,299 --> 00:33:50,900
Wait, that's wiretapped.

428
00:33:50,900 --> 00:33:52,000
It's on airplane mode.

429
00:33:57,009 --> 00:33:58,309
When did you take this?

430
00:33:59,910 --> 00:34:02,180
- You might die.
- Mr. Moon.

431
00:34:02,309 --> 00:34:03,410
What do you find strange?

432
00:34:07,220 --> 00:34:08,280
Please help me.

433
00:34:17,860 --> 00:34:18,929
She moved first.

434
00:34:38,179 --> 00:34:39,179
Yes, Senior Superintendent Han.

435
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,519
It's me, Old Man.

436
00:34:40,519 --> 00:34:42,050
Hey, where were you hiding?

437
00:34:42,050 --> 00:34:43,820
Senior Superintendent Han
was worried.

438
00:34:43,820 --> 00:34:44,849
Where's Seo Yi Soo?

439
00:34:45,090 --> 00:34:46,389
At Bang Jun Seok's.

440
00:34:46,860 --> 00:34:49,260
We'll be right there, so keep
watching her. Where's Se Hoon?

441
00:34:49,429 --> 00:34:50,659
He's not here.

442
00:34:51,159 --> 00:34:53,800
- Why not?
- He's trying to save you.

443
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:55,230
What do you mean?

444
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:58,429
What do you think? He's trying
to be a good partner to you.

445
00:34:58,429 --> 00:35:00,139
("Dong Baek Suspected
to Be a Serial Killer")

446
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:03,039
This article is from us.

447
00:35:07,039 --> 00:35:08,179
You know this is not true.

448
00:35:09,079 --> 00:35:10,179
I'm sorry.

449
00:35:11,550 --> 00:35:14,050
I'm not asking you to sugarcoat it.
We just want you to write the truth.

450
00:35:14,719 --> 00:35:17,449
Can't you just write about Dong Baek
as he is?

451
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,219
I have no excuses.

452
00:35:29,369 --> 00:35:30,570
Det. Oh.

453
00:35:38,070 --> 00:35:40,579
- The day I got appointed,
- Thank you for the food!

454
00:35:41,079 --> 00:35:42,210
Enjoy.

455
00:35:42,349 --> 00:35:44,250
I saw Baek for the first time.

456
00:35:46,349 --> 00:35:49,119
Gosh, this month has been so busy.

457
00:35:49,119 --> 00:35:50,190
I know, right?

458
00:35:50,190 --> 00:35:51,789
I suddenly got a strange feeling.

459
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:53,820
- The noodles are good.
- We should check that.

460
00:35:54,519 --> 00:35:55,889
What kind of feeling?

461
00:35:57,260 --> 00:35:58,630
He looked lonely.

462
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:01,460
We should do it before then.

463
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:07,670
Salute.

464
00:36:08,940 --> 00:36:10,510
It's an honor to meet you.

465
00:36:10,739 --> 00:36:12,280
May I ask for a handshake?

466
00:36:16,809 --> 00:36:17,909
Yes.

467
00:36:22,849 --> 00:36:25,349
Constable Oh Se Hoon.

468
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:28,019
What?

469
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:39,539
Gosh.

470
00:36:39,670 --> 00:36:43,110
People talked behind our backs
and called us crazy,

471
00:36:43,909 --> 00:36:45,010
but I...

472
00:36:47,409 --> 00:36:49,110
just felt sorry for Baek.

473
00:36:54,719 --> 00:36:56,750
Hey. You can have all of these.

474
00:36:57,590 --> 00:36:59,860
Really? Thank you!

475
00:37:06,900 --> 00:37:09,030
He wouldn't let anyone
get close to him.

476
00:37:10,699 --> 00:37:14,599
But he gave you so much love.

477
00:37:15,869 --> 00:37:18,170
Do you know why Baek
started to act like a celebrity?

478
00:37:24,150 --> 00:37:26,679
I can't say he wasn't
narcissistic before,

479
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:32,659
but it's because of
the criminals' memories.

480
00:37:34,119 --> 00:37:35,320
The criminals?

481
00:37:37,829 --> 00:37:39,429
Evil memories...

482
00:37:40,500 --> 00:37:42,300
can't be erased easily...

483
00:37:43,829 --> 00:37:45,599
once they're read.

484
00:37:47,570 --> 00:37:50,239
The pains of the victims
that Baek read...

485
00:37:51,070 --> 00:37:54,539
can be consoled a little bit
when the culprit is caught.

486
00:37:55,750 --> 00:37:58,710
But the memories of the criminals
are the opposite.

487
00:38:00,550 --> 00:38:02,219
They only get clearer.

488
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:06,489
Whenever that happened,
people's love...

489
00:38:07,190 --> 00:38:08,860
was the only thing
that helped him stay strong.

490
00:38:09,489 --> 00:38:11,659
- Hello.
- You're here.

491
00:38:11,659 --> 00:38:13,929
- I'm her dad.
- I see.

492
00:38:13,929 --> 00:38:15,199
Thank you so much.

493
00:38:16,130 --> 00:38:19,469
If it wasn't for you,
it would've been hard on her.

494
00:38:20,099 --> 00:38:21,639
You should hurry and thank him.

495
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,840
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

496
00:38:24,110 --> 00:38:26,079
I made these macarons.

497
00:38:26,139 --> 00:38:28,739
They cried while thanking him
for catching the criminal.

498
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:30,010
Thank you.

499
00:38:32,250 --> 00:38:35,550
Letters from the victims' families
cheered him up.

500
00:38:39,619 --> 00:38:42,360
He may seem like he's always
dressing up and boasting,

501
00:38:45,489 --> 00:38:48,460
but he was struggling by himself
as he was rotting inside.

502
00:38:56,570 --> 00:38:58,309
I was called by
the disciplinary committee too.

503
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:02,409
But, I don't mind.

504
00:39:03,750 --> 00:39:06,219
I can't even protect my partner,
so how can I protect the country?

505
00:39:08,179 --> 00:39:10,250
If something happens to Baek,

506
00:39:12,019 --> 00:39:13,559
I'll quit my job.

507
00:39:15,590 --> 00:39:16,889
Even if I get expelled,

508
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:19,929
I'll make sure to stay by his side.

509
00:39:27,469 --> 00:39:28,800
Thank you for your time.

510
00:39:59,570 --> 00:40:01,570
Seo Yi Soo hasn't come out
after going into the house.

511
00:40:01,699 --> 00:40:03,539
You haven't found Cheon Ki Soo
or Moon Yong Gwang?

512
00:40:03,840 --> 00:40:05,369
I'll start looking again.

513
00:40:05,369 --> 00:40:07,940
No, the RIU is chasing them as well.

514
00:40:07,940 --> 00:40:10,780
I want you to keep your eyes
on Deputy Chief Lee's family.

515
00:40:11,309 --> 00:40:12,519
"Deputy Chief Lee's family"?

516
00:40:13,449 --> 00:40:16,750
The Eraser is killing the families
related to the Shimbae case.

517
00:40:17,550 --> 00:40:19,260
He'll target Mr. Lee's family too.

518
00:40:19,619 --> 00:40:20,659
Why?

